adrFormatAddress: 834 5th Ave, New York, NY 10065, USA

originalText.text:
The luxury 16-story limestone-clad apartment building 834 Fifth Avenue, located on Manhattan’s Upper East Side between East 64th and East 65th Streets, is considered the finest building by noted architect Rosario Candela. It has very large apartments including many duplexes and a triplex with outdoor terraces.

The building ranks as perhaps the most exclusive pre-War cooperative apartment building in New York City. No financing is allowed--all cash is required to purchase an apartment and all prospective tenants must have at least ten times the selling price in liquid assets. 834 Fifth Avenue's cooperative board is highly selective. There are also hefty monthly maintenance fees.

Notable tenants have included Laurence Rockefeller, Watson K. Blair and Rupert Murdock.

I have known several people who have lived in duplex apartments at 834 Fifth Avenue. I admired the exclusivity, the understated lobby and white-gloved doormen and elevator attendants and, of course, the grand and beautiful apartments.

The residences all have 12+ foot high ceilings, private elevator landings leading to spacious entrance foyers, very large salons with fireplaces, powder rooms, walk-in closets, libraries, formal dining rooms, butlers' pantries, laundry rooms, huge kitchens and multiple staff bedrooms. Some apartments have dumbwaiters and all have wine cellars, multiple storage rooms and fireplaces. There is no parking garage, health club, private restaurant or roof-top terrace for tenants.

There are white-gloved elevator operators to bring you up to the various apartments' large entrance foyers, with impressive staircases to the second level of the duplexes.

The views of Fifth Avenue, Central Park, the Children's Zoo and across the park of Central Park West are exceptional.
